# DEDI Client Refactoring Rules

## Context
This is a Flutter Matrix client rebrand: Twake → Dedi, Linagora → DediApp
Project: /Users/liberyus/development/dedi
Domain: dedim.com.tr
Organization: DediApp
Platform: Flutter/Dart multi-platform

## IMPORTANT: FVM Usage
This project uses FVM (Flutter Version Management) to handle version compatibility.
ALL Flutter commands must be prefixed with `fvm`:
- `fvm flutter pub get` (not `flutter pub get`)
- `fvm flutter test` (not `flutter test`)
- `fvm flutter build apk` (not `flutter build apk`)

## When refactoring:

### 0. Memorize everything
- Keep the files up to date:
````
TESTFLIGHT_BRANDING_PLAN.md
docs/UNIFIED_IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE.md
docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md
docs/MIGRATION_ACHIEVEMENTS.md
docs/COMPLETE PHONE AUTH IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE FOR TWAKE CHAT.md
docs/PHONE AUTH IMPLEMENTATION STATUS UPDATE.md
docs/refactoring/DEDI_CLIENT_REFACTORING_PLAN.md
````
- Always commit changes
- Use task-master and it's commands for task tracking

### 1. Package Names
- Always use @dedi/* instead of @twake/*
- Update pubspec.yaml dependencies
- Update import statements accordingly
- Keep matrix-dart-sdk unchanged (Matrix protocol compliance)

### 2. Class Naming
- TwakeSomething → DediSomething
- Keep Matrix* classes unchanged (Matrix protocol compliance)
- Keep core Flutter functionality intact
- Keep native login flow intact (already implemented)

### 3. API Endpoints
- New endpoints use /_dedi/ prefix
- Add backwards compatibility for /_twake/
- Add deprecation headers
- Log deprecated endpoint usage
- Support both until 2025-06-01

### 4. URLs and Domains
- twake.app → dedim.com.tr
- sign-up.twake.app → sign-up.dedim.com.tr
- linagora/* → dediapp/*
- ci.linagora.com → github.com

### 5. DO NOT CHANGE (CRITICAL)
- Matrix protocol implementations (matrix-dart-sdk)
- Core Flutter functionality
- Native login flow (SplashView, OnboardingView, PhoneInputView, OTPVerifyView)
- Matrix client-server API compliance
- SMS multi-provider integration

### 6. DEDI Custom Features (PRESERVE)
- Native login flow (already implemented)
- SMS multi-provider support (backend integration)
- Turkish SMS providers integration
- dedi://login deep link
- dedim.com.tr URLs (already configured)

### 7. Configuration Updates
- twake_chat → dedi_chat (config keys)
- Application names: "Twake Chat" → "Dedi Chat"
- Package names in pubspec.yaml
- Asset file names and references

### 8. Flutter-Specific Updates
- Update pubspec.yaml package names
- Update config.json branding
- Update assets (logos, icons, branding)
- Update platform-specific configurations
- Update localization files

## Code Style
- Dart with strict types
- 2-space indentation
- Single quotes for strings
- Descriptive variable names
- Comprehensive documentation
- Follow Dart/Flutter conventions

## Testing
After any refactoring:
- Run: fvm flutter test
- Run: fvm flutter test integration_test/
- Run: fvm flutter build apk
- Run: fvm flutter build web
- Check: No twake.app references remain
- Verify: API compatibility maintained
- Test: SMS functionality works
- Validate: All platform builds succeed

## Risk Management
- Always create backups before changes
- Test on all platforms (Android, iOS, Web, Desktop)
- Coordinate with server team for API changes
- Document all breaking changes
- Provide rollback procedures

## File Patterns
- Update imports: from 'package:twake_' → from 'package:dedi_'
- Update classes: class TwakeX → class DediX
- Update variables: twakeX → dediX
- Update constants: TWAKE_X → DEDI_X
- Update comments: "Twake" → "Dedi"
- Update assets: twake_* → dedi_*

## Validation Commands
```bash
# Check for remaining twake references
grep -r "twake" lib/
grep -r "twake.app" lib/

# Verify new dedi references
grep -r "dedi" lib/
grep -r "dedim.com.tr" lib/

# Check API endpoints
grep -r "/_dedi/" lib/

# Validate Flutter build (using FVM)
fvm flutter test
fvm flutter build apk
fvm flutter build web
```

## Emergency Rollback
If issues occur:
```bash
git reset --hard HEAD~1
fvm flutter clean
fvm flutter pub get
fvm flutter test
```

## Success Criteria
- All Flutter tests pass
- All platform builds succeed
- No twake references remain
- API backwards compatibility works
- SMS functionality preserved
- Matrix protocol compliance maintained
- Native login flow preserved

## Platform-Specific Considerations
- **Android**: Update app name, package name, icons in android/
- **iOS**: Update app name, bundle identifier, icons in ios/
- **Web**: Update title, favicon, manifest in web/
- **Desktop**: Update app names and icons for Linux, macOS, Windows

## Asset Management
- Update all logo files in assets/
- Update app icons for all platforms
- Update splash screen assets
- Update loading animations
- Update branding images

## Localization Updates
- Update Turkish translations in assets/l10n/
- Update app names in all languages
- Update branding strings
- Update error messages
